STEP 4 — Wire form submit through preview → confirm/cancel
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Currently form_submit_handler_node inserts directly into DB.
Change it to:

1. Validate all fields (existing validation code — unchanged).
2. On validation failure: return form_errors event (unchanged).
3. On validation success:
   a. Do NOT insert into DB yet.
   b. Build a pending_mrr_data dict in the SAME format that the
      Excel handler uses (so mrr_submission_node can process it).
   c. Generate the MRR number (next_id from sequence).
   d. Build the preview message via _build_mrr_preview_message.
   e. Return:
        {
            "messages": [AIMessage(content=preview_message)],
            "pending_mrr_data": pending_dict,
            "execution_log": ...
