NOTES
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Thread_id frontend requirement: the frontend MUST send back the
  same thread_id on the confirm turn. Without it, the checkpointer
  loads empty state and pending_mrr_data is None. The confirm will
  then fail with "No MRR data to submit." Document this clearly in
  the report — frontend must implement thread_id resend before
  end-to-end testing works.
- MemorySaver vs SqliteSaver: MemorySaver works for single-process
  testing. SqliteSaver persists across server restarts. Use
  SqliteSaver if available; MemorySaver as fallback.
- The checkpointer is PER WORKFLOW. RMS and HRMS do NOT get a
  checkpointer in this task. Only MRR.
- Static_output_nodes: form_submit_handler_node is already in both
  lists. After this change it no longer returns a final message
  directly (it returns the preview). The preview message goes
  through the same static_output_nodes path. No change needed.
- If existing tests break (RMS, HRMS, MRR approval flows), check
  whether the thread_id config is being passed correctly. Non-MRR
  workflows don't use a checkpointer so they're unaffected.

